         <div type="edition" ana="#b1" xml:lang="grc" subtype="transcription" xml:id="zoor0270.transcription" corresp="#zoor0270.translation">
            <p><g type="cross">+</g>
               <lb/>
               <choice><orig>Μνημῖον</orig><reg>Μνημεῖον</reg></choice>
               <lb/> Μιλίχου<lb/> Ἀβδάλγου,<lb/> ἀποθανὼν<lb/> ἐτῶν <num>κηʹ</num>.<lb/>
               <choice><orig>Θάρσι</orig><reg>Θάρσει</reg></choice>, <choice><orig>οὐδὶ<lb break="no"/>ς</orig><reg>οὐδείς</reg></choice>
               <expan><abbr>ἀ<unclear>θ</unclear>άνατ<am>ϛ</am></abbr><ex>ος</ex></expan>
               <lb/>
               <g type="cross">+</g></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" ana="#b1" xml:id="zoor0270.translation" corresp="#zoor0270.transcription">
            <p>Monument of Milichos, (son) of Abdalges, who died (at the age) of 28 years. Be of
                    good cheer, no one (is) immortal.</p>
         </div>
      <div type="edition" subtype="transcription_segmented"><p> <orig xml:id="zoor0270-1" xml:lang="grc">Μνημῖον</orig> <w xml:id="zoor0270-2" xml:lang="grc">Μιλίχου</w> <w xml:id="zoor0270-3" xml:lang="grc">Ἀβδάλγου,</w> <w xml:id="zoor0270-4" xml:lang="grc">ἀποθανὼν</w> <w xml:id="zoor0270-5" xml:lang="grc">ἐτῶν</w> <num xml:id="zoor0270-6" xml:lang="grc">κηʹ</num> <orig xml:id="zoor0270-7" xml:lang="grc">Θάρσι</orig> <orig xml:id="zoor0270-8" xml:lang="grc">οὐδὶς</orig> <w xml:id="zoor0270-9" xml:lang="grc"><expan><abbr>ἀ<unclear>θ</unclear>άνατ<am>ϛ</am></abbr><ex>ος</ex></expan></w> </p>
</div>
</body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>No date is provided in the inscription, but it has been dated to the second half of
               the fourth century CE on the strength of other factors. The tombstone is one of about
               700 discovered in Byzantine Zoora. The majority of the Greek tombstones from this
               location have been identified as Christian. The author notes that the names in this
               inscription also appear elsewhere at Ghor es-Safi. The text contains spelling and
               grammatical errors.</p>
         </div>
